What this scaffold really is

This is not yet a full Kapnet node. It is a coherent Rust-shaped protocol skeleton. In other words, it already has the beginnings of:
	•	a canonical message object,
	•	a weakwork admission path,
	•	a braid structure for organizing message flow,
	•	a knot/checkpoint format,
	•	a constitution and permission model,
	•	a deterministic bounded VM,
	•	a global state accumulator,
	•	and a relay node that ties those pieces together.

That matters because it means the code is not just random type definitions. It already sketches a state transition pipeline:
	1.	a user forms a TXXM,
	2.	the TXXM can carry script,
	3.	the TXXM can be associated with weakwork,
	4.	a relay checks policy,
	5.	accepted messages enter local state,
	6.	accepted messages are inserted into a braid,
	7.	the braid can be summarized into knot claims,
	8.	the global state can be root-committed.

That is already a very Kapnet-ish architecture.

