7. knot.rs: checkpoint formation

This module defines the scaffold’s checkpoint object.

KnotHeader

Contains:
	•	version,
	•	base chain ID,
	•	base block hash,
	•	braid root,
	•	auxpow root,
	•	state root,
	•	height,
	•	timestamp.

This is already extremely close to the kind of structure you would want for a Kapnet knot claim.

It ties together:
	•	where on the base chain you are anchored,
	•	what braid view you are committing to,
	•	what auxiliary work universe you are acknowledging,
	•	what state root results from that view.

That is a very good start.

KnotClaim

Contains:
	•	header,
	•	explicit list of entries,
	•	signer,
	•	optional signature.

This is effectively a proposal or claim about a checkpoint.

digest()

Commits to:
	•	header digest,
	•	entries Merkle root,
	•	signer,
	•	signature if present.

This is strong because it means the knot claim is itself hash-addressable.

knot_from_braid(...)

This helper builds a knot from:
	•	a braid,
	•	a base chain label,
	•	a base block hash,
	•	an auxpow root,
	•	a state root,
	•	height and timestamp.

This is a nice bridge between the relay-local world and the checkpoint world.

