Contains:
	•	guilds map
	•	orphan messages

The orphan concept is important: not all messages successfully land in a room. Some are routed more loosely.

⸻

State methods

ensure_guild()
Creates a guild if absent.

ensure_room()
Creates a room within a guild if absent.

add_member()
Adds a principal to a room.

This is simple, but it already implies room-local membership handling.

apply_txxm()
This is the important one.

It:
	•	computes the message ID,
	•	iterates over destinations,
	•	routes guild-targeted messages to guild existence plus orphan store,
	•	routes room messages to concrete rooms,
	•	checks sender membership for room posting,
	•	appends accepted submissions to the room,
	•	pushes unrouted items into orphan storage.

This is effectively the current state transition function for incoming TXXMs.

Important behavior

For room messages, the sender must already be a member of that room.

That is a meaningful governance gate.

root()

Computes a Merkle root over guild-level state summaries.

This gives a commitment surface for:
	•	checkpointing,
	•	comparison,
	•	replay validation.

