⸻

ingest(...)

This is the main pipeline.

It:
	1.	checks body size,
	2.	requires weakwork if policy says so,
	3.	validates the weakwork,
	4.	checks the score against relay threshold,
	5.	applies the TXXM to state,
	6.	stores it in mempool,
	7.	creates a braid entry using current braid tips as parents,
	8.	inserts the entry into the braid,
	9.	returns the ID.

This is the current best single summary of the whole scaffold.

In plain language:

a relay admits a message under local policy, updates governed state, and folds the message into a weighted coordination DAG.

That is already a serious architecture.

build_checkpoint_candidates(limit)

This sorts tips by cumulative braid weight and returns the top ones.

This is a primitive checkpoint candidate selector.

