How I would interpret this scaffold philosophically

This code is not trying to make Bitcoin into a smart-contract chain.

It is doing something more interesting.

It is modeling a world where:
	•	Bitcoin remains the external anchor,
	•	messages become structured social-economic actions,
	•	relays become policy-enforcing coordinators,
	•	governance becomes executable and hash-committed,
	•	ordering becomes a weighted braid,
	•	checkpoints become knots.

That is very close to your recurring formulation that Kapnet is a replayable, leaderless, cyphereconomic coordination layer over base-chain time and anchoring.

